                                        <h6>Henry Buffalow<span class="person-title">Service Manager</span></h6>
                                      <p>Henry Buffalow holds a BS in Environmental Engineering from Cal Poly, San Luis Obispo and a Master in Business Administration from Pepperdine University, Malibu, CA. He joined his father out of college and used the skills learned to do air conditioning and refrigeration design, estimating, project management and running the business. After 24 years he closed the company to experience new ventures. First, as a Facilities Manger for a high tech firm supervising all their mechanical systems and supervision of construction of a new class 10 clean room. Then he moved on to working with Honeywell as an energy saving engineer evaluating large system energy consumption and indoor air quality audits and policies. Recognizing that he preferred entrepreneurial pursuits he started a new HVAC service business. Later the firm would be merged with Buffalo’s Mechanical and he became the Service Manager 
</p>
<p>Among his many awards and recognitions includes:<br />
Certified Energy Manager – Association of Energy Engineers<br />
Certified Demand Side Energy Manager – Association of Energy Engineers<br />
Energy Engineer of the Year 2002 – Association of Energy Engineers <br />
Solar Pioneer Award from SMACNA 1977<br />

</p>
<p>Other Activities
Current member of Cupertino Rotary. Sits on the Foundation Board and is active in many community service activities
Served on The Board of California Sheetmetal Contractors holding all local and state offices and as a member of the National SMACNA board
Served on the Board of the Air Conditioning & Refrigeration Contractors and Air Conditioning Contractors Association
Served on the board and held office with Kiwanis of Mountain View, CA, Association of Energy Engineers, Silicon Valley Engineers, Association of Facilities Engineers
Past Chairman City of Cupertino Energy Commission
</p>
                                        <p>Henry has been married 47 years and enjoys significant time with his wife Susan, two kids and four grandkids. Outdoor sports of all types have been mandatory. He practices “Service above Self” through his Rotary activities</p>
